# Linux Server Hardening & Security Optimization

## Author

Saurabh Singh

## Project Number

Project 01

## Environment

* Cloud Platform: AWS EC2
* Operating System: Red Hat Enterprise Linux (RHEL 10)
* Package Manager: DNF
* Firewall: Firewalld
* SSH Service: OpenSSH
* User Management: Linux Local Users
* Logging: systemd-journald

---

# 1. Objective

The objective of this project was to harden a newly provisioned Linux server by implementing production-grade security best practices. The project focused on minimizing the server's attack surface, implementing secure user access controls, configuring firewall rules, enforcing password policies, securing SSH access, and validating the server through logging and auditing.

---

