* timedatectl
* dnf history

---

## Phase 2 – User & Group Management

Created Groups

* devops
* developers
* auditors

Created Users

* devopsadmin
* developer
* readonly

Verification

* id
* groups
* /etc/passwd
* /etc/group

---

## Phase 3 – Sudo Configuration

Implemented Principle of Least Privilege.

Administrative privileges were granted only to the devopsadmin account through the wheel group.

Developer and Readonly users were intentionally restricted from using sudo.

Verification

* sudo -l
* id username

---

## Phase 4 – SSH Hardening

Security Controls

* Disabled Root Login
* Disabled Empty Passwords
* Limited Authentication Attempts
* Configured Idle Session Timeout
* Validated SSH Configuration

Verification

* sshd -t
* systemctl status sshd

---

## Phase 5 – Firewall Configuration

Configured Firewalld to allow only

* SSH
* HTTP
* HTTPS

All unnecessary services remained blocked.

Verification

* firewall-cmd --list-all

---

## Phase 6 – Password Policy

Implemented

* Maximum Password Age
* Minimum Password Age
* Password Warning
* Account Lockout

Verification

